Interface FilopodyanProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ALTProcessor, LoGProcessor

    public interface FilopodyanProcessor
    Implemented by classes for processing an image to create a binary mask
    Author:
    Richard Butler

    • Method Detail

      • process

        ij.ImagePlus process(ij.ImagePlus imp,
                     int chan,
                     int t0,
                     int t1,
                     double sigma,
                     java.lang.String threshold,
                     boolean verbose)
        The method implementing processing
        Parameters:
        imp - the image to process, not changed by the processing
        chan - the channel to process
        t0 - the start index of the time range to process (inclusive)
        t1 - the end index of the time range to process (inclusive)
        sigma - the Gaussian sigma value
        threshold - the ImageJ thresholding method to use to create the binary mask from the processed image
        verbose - true to log additional information including the LoG kernel
        Returns:
        a binary mask created by this method
